FT  09 OCT 92 / World Trade News: Lucas and Sagem link
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LUCAS Industries and Sagem, the French defence, telecommunications,
electronics and motor components group, are forming a joint venture aimed at
capturing 10 per cent of Europe's Pounds 900m-a-year petrol engine
management systems market, John Griffiths writes.
Tighter exhaust emissions controls and the development of technically more
advanced car engines are seen by the partners as giving the potential for
engine management systems to become one of the fastest growing automotive
components sectors.
Lucas also said last night it was undertaking its first motor components
venture in eastern Europe, a Czech manufacturing operation which would
initially produce braking systems for car maker VW-Skoda.
