FT  09 OCT 92 / International Company News: Fannie Mae profits crack record
again
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE FEDERAL National Mortgage Association (Fannie Mae) yesterday reported
third-quarter net income of Dollars 412.9m, the 19th consecutive
record-breaking quarter for the company, the largest mortgage provider in
the US.
Fannie Mae's latest result beat the record of Dollars 402m in the second
quarter, and easily outdistanced the Dollars 350.7m earned at the same stage
of 1991.
Mr James Johnson, chairman, said the performance was fuelled by strong
growth in mortgage-backed securities (MBS) issuance, which totalled Dollars
41.3bn, and record fees from sales of Remics (real estate mortgage
investment conduits), which helped offset a decline in net interest income
from Dollars 518.2m to Dollars 506.9m.
Fannie Mae's net interest margin fell in the quarter from 139 basis points
to 133 basis points.
Provisions for losses were Dollars 80m in the quarter, the same as the
previous period, taking total provisions to Dollars 765.8m.
In response, its shares rose Dollars 1 3/8 to Dollars 64 3/4 in New York.
The Student Loan Marketing Association (Sallie Mae) yesterday reported a 15
per cent improvement in third-quarter profits to Dollars 100m, or Dollars
1.08 a share. The strong profits performance sent Sallie Mae shares Dollars
1 1/2 higher to Dollars 70 1/2 .
