FT  09 OCT 92 / Move to end power plant walkout
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
UNION officials will meet shop stewards this morning in an attempt to
resolve an unofficial walkout by more than 2,000 workers that has halted
construction of the Enron gas-fired power plant, Teeside, Chris Tighe
writes.
The workers - employed by the main contractor, Wimpey, and nearly 20
subcontractors - walked out on Monday in a protest over safety standards.
Enron Power Corporation said the safety issues had been addressed but the
men refused to return until Monday unless they received full payment for the
hours they had lost. The company had offered 10 hours money a man.
Enron has warned that the men are in breach of agreements and are risking
dismissal. Teesside officials of the main unions involved will today urge
the men to return to work immediately.
Construction of the plant, at Imperial Chemical Industries' Wilton site,
began nearly two years ago and is due to finish in January.
