</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Argentine economy minister Domingo Cavallo has announced a package to reduce
business costs, writes John Barham in Buenos Aires.
Among the measures are a cap on interest rates of 27 per cent a year at
state banks, a reduction in employers' social security contributions, and a
further round of deregulation. Also, new tax rebates and incentives aim to
encourage exports and imports of capital goods. Initial estimates put the
cost of the package at the equivalent of more than Dollars 1.3bn a year.
