<DOCNO>FT924-14632</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-CJHBUACOFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>921008
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  08 OCT 92 / People: Moves in finance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After 37 years in the business, David Lumsden this week retired from the
broking firm which bears his name, Henry Cooke Lumsden, having seen it
develop into one of the UK's biggest regional stockbroking firms. Lumsden,
61, joined the family firm of Lumsden &amp; Co in the City in 1955, eventually
merging the firm with Manchester-based Henry Cooke in 1973. Since then,
Lumsden has acted as managing director of the firm's London offices.
