<HEADLINE>
FT  08 OCT 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Unlike the currencies in which it is traded, wool is maintaining steady
price levels in the primary markets. There have been good clearances in
Australia this week, with Japan the leading buyer. The relative firmness
does not, however, indicate buoyancy in user industries or consumer markets.
Price changes in the UK market for tops are again due more to currency
movements than to any shift in market conditions. Business is very quiet and
the only signs of real improvement are on the export front.
</TEXT>
