Earnings per share fell from 12.2p to 5.26p but the group will pay a final
dividend of 3.25p, making a total for the year of 4.75p.
After Pounds 13m of capital expenditure on its Megabowl, including two new
sites at Preston and Dundee, net debt has risen to Pounds 14.3m.
As a result gearing has risen to 51 per cent from 24 per cent last year. Mr
Duncan Moss, finance director said the company aimed to maintain gearing
below 55 per cent.
Then group has made a Pounds 304,000 provision covering future costs
relating to the stand-alone theme bars which are to be sold and have been
written off in the accounts.
